//! Same-bare-name type fixture (narrow layout). Exports a `Widget` record whose
//! sole field is an `i8`. A sibling package `hew::widgeti64` exports a `Widget`
//! of the same bare name carrying an `i64` — a divergent layout. Importing both
//! exercises the cross-package bare-name collision in the MIR `RecordLayout`
//! registry: keying a type's layout/field order by its bare name lets the second
//! module's `Widget` clobber the first, so a field load against the surviving
//! layout trips the codegen fail-closed. The fix derives each type's layout
//! through its module-qualified identity, not the last-write-wins bare key.

/// Narrow `Widget`: a single `i8` field.
type Widget {
    v: i8;
}
